<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                        <head>189. Note From the White House Staff Secretary (<persName corresp="#p_CJE_1" type="from">Connor</persName>) to President
                                <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1" type="to">Ford</persName><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d189fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Ford</persName> Library, Staff Secretary’s Office, Presidential
                                Handwriting File, Box 6, Subject File, Countries, Angola. No
                                classification marking.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1976-05-11">May 11, 1976</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <opener>
                            <salute>Mr President:</salute>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="center">Application for <gloss target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss>
                            Membership by Angola</p>
                        <p>Jack Marsh made the following recommendation on the attached memo from
                                <persName corresp="#p_SBC_1">Brent Scowcroft</persName>:<note n="2" xml:id="d189fn2">
                                <ref target="#d188">Document 188</ref>.</note>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Veto but subject to approval by withdrawal of Cuban troops when
                                    and if withdrawal occurs.”<note n="3" xml:id="d189fn3">See <ref target="#d191fn4">footnote 4, Document 191</ref>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>We are attempting to obtain a reaction on this subject from <persName corresp="#p_AT_1">Tim Austin</persName> but this has not been
                            received at this writing.<note n="4" xml:id="d189fn4">Another note from
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Connor</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Ford</persName>, May 11, reads: “Just heard
                                from <persName corresp="#p_AT_1">Tim Austin</persName>—the feeling
                                from his area is they concur in the recommendation to abstain.”
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Ford</persName> Library, Staff
                                Secretary’s Office, Presidential Handwriting File, Box 6, Subject
                                File, Countries, Angola)</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>We have just been notified by the <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                            that <gloss target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss> will begin discussion of this
                            subject at 10:30 this morning, therefore, this paper requires immediate
                                action.<note n="5" xml:id="d189fn5">A note from <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Connor</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_SBC_1">Scowcroft</persName>, May 11, reads: “We have
                                been informed the President gave Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SWW_1">Scranton</persName> verbal orders to veto.”
                                (Ibid.)</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Jim Connor</hi>
                                </persName><note n="6" xml:id="d189fn6">Printed from a copy that
                                    bears this typed signature.</note>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>